  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nI have code that uses `truffle-contract` for interacting with smart contract. It should work in Node.js and browser so I use [AEgir](https://www.npmjs.com/package/aegir) to build it for browser (with Webpack).\r\n\r\nIt works normally in Node.js but there are problems in the browser.\r\n\r\nWhen I include my built JS file, I get error `Cannot find module 'xmlhttprequest'` and none of my code works.\r\n\r\nIt looks like request for module `xmlhttprequest` come from package `ethers`, more specifically [`ethers/utils/web`](https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/master/utils/web.js#L10), and Webpack didn't resolve module into browser's code.\r\n\r\nI think that worked in previous versions of `truffle-contract`.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know how to fix this or if this is issue with AEgir, Webpack or Ethers.\r\n\r\n## Screenshots\r\n\r\n![error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16626308/50728588-a1112780-112c-11e9-8ea0-ac727300174e.png)\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Browser: Firefox and Chrome\r\n* Truffle Contract: 4.0.1\r\n* AEgir: 18.0.2\r\n",
